# Task router — Update Customer Notes

## When this rule applies

- The user opens or references **`docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md`**, or
- The user (or chat) clearly invokes **`Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`**, **`UCN for [CustomerName]`**, or informal **`UCN`** / **`ucn`** when the customer is already fixed in context (any reasonable casing/spacing for the customer token), or
- The user invokes an **alias** trigger (same **`[CustomerName]`** token): **`Update Customer Notes with Challenge Review first for [CustomerName]`** or **`Lifecycle-first Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`** (same as default UCN — see **`.cursor/rules/20-orchestrator.mdc`**), or
- The user invokes an **opt-out** trigger: **`Update Customer Notes (no challenge review) for [CustomerName]`**, **`UCN without challenge review for [CustomerName]`**, or **`Light UCN for [CustomerName]`**.

Repo-wide planner/orchestrator behavior stays in **`.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc`** (main Agent). This file only **routes product workflows**; it does **not** redefine subagent delegation or task-plan approval.

## Preferred path: multi-advisor orchestrator

When the user wants the **full Stage 3 pipeline**, follow **`.cursor/rules/20-orchestrator.mdc`** end-to-end. **Default UCN** includes **Phase 0** (Challenge Review through the review table + **Block A** proposals, no writes until approval) → sync and steps **1–7** (structured context through compile) → **one combined STOP** (Block A + Block B) → execute **A** (if approved) then **B** (if approved). **Opt-out** UCN skips Phase 0 and uses a **legacy** single STOP (Block B only), per **`20-orchestrator.mdc`**.

Treat **`[CustomerName]`** as the single customer for the session (**`docs/project_spec.md` §2 Rule 4**). If missing, ask once before deep reads.

## Fallback: monolithic playbook

**`docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md`** remains a **supported, documented fallback** when you need the **legacy monolithic** step list. Use it when:

- The user explicitly asks for the **legacy / single-pass** playbook, or
- They need only a subset of steps from that doc without advisor fan-out.

If intent is ambiguous, **prefer** **`20-orchestrator.mdc`** and say so in one line; offer the monolithic playbook as the alternative.

